				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When the timer is clocked while the counter's value is 0, the MMC3 loads the period value into the counter, and the /IRQ signal goes low. This means RTI from the IRQ handler will just result in another IRQ because the /IRQ signal is still low. Acknowledging the interrupt allows /IRQ to go high again.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
